As part   of the Underground Works Department, you will be part of a team to develop   Singapore’s underground master plan. This will involve working closely with our land planners and with partner agencies on policies and processes for the planning and development of underground space, as well as overseeing the development of a new IT system and database to support the underground master plan. You will provide civil engineering and geotechnical expertise for underground development works and contribute to feasibility studies of related infrastructure works.
 

Requirements:


  Possess strong quantitative, analytical skills and basic financial knowledge
  Familiarity with GIS, CAD, BIM will be an advantage
  Familiarity with software engineering analysis program e.g. plaxis 
  Good interpersonal and communication skills
  Strong report writing and presentation skills
